Class TypeCache<T extends SonarObject>

java.lang.Object
us.mn.state.dot.sonar.client.TypeCache<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>
public class TypeCache<T extends SonarObject> extends Object implements Iterable<T>
A type cache represents the first-level nodes in the SONAR namespace. It contains all proxy objects of the given type.
Author:
Douglas Lau

  • Constructor Details

    • TypeCache

      public TypeCache(Class iface, Client c) throws NoSuchFieldException, IllegalAccessException
      Create a type cache. NOTE: because of limitations with generics and reflection, the interface must be passed to the constructor in addition to the <T> qualifier. These types must be identical! For example, to create a cache of Users, do this: new TypeCache<User>(User.class, client)
      Parameters:
      iface - Interface extending SonarObject.
      c - Sonar Client.
      Throws:
      NoSuchFieldException
      IllegalAccessException
